title: Franchise value of the Los Angeles Clippers ( NBA ) 2003 to 2020
yAxis: Franchise value in million U.S. dollars
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Franchise value in million U.S. dollars, containing a total of 18 data points.
Overall Franchise value in million U.S. dollars has increased over the Year.

Franchise value in million U.S. dollars is roughly constant from 2003 to 2012, rapidly increasing from 2012 to 2016, roughly constant from 2016 to 2019, and finally roughly increasing from 2019 to 2020.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2014 and 2015.
Maximum Franchise value in million U.S. dollars, about 2600.0 was reported at Year 2020
The lowest Franchise value in million U.S. dollars, of value 205.0 was reported at Year 2003
